&lt;p&gt;Part Time: .2 WTE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 8a&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Title : Course Lead for Tavistock/Gloucester Counselling Service Course &#39;PG Cert in Child, Adolescent and Family Mental Wellbeing: Multidisciplinary Practice&#39; (D24G)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at GCS in Stroud, must be available Thursdays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to lead a well-established course that is part of a growing partnership between GCS and the Tavistock and Portman NHS Foundation Trust. As a multi-modal course drawing on both psychodynamic and systemic practice as well as a developmental framework, we welcome applicants with professional qualifications in either psychoanalytic/psychodynamic or systemic psychotherapy as well as a core profession.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Course Lead for D24G will be responsible for managing and leading this innovative tri-modal Post graduate certificate course, aimed at anyone working with adolescents and adults, be this in the statutory, educational or voluntary sector. The course draws on psychodynamic, systemic and developmental frameworks, and shares teaching and learning with another post graduate course, aimed at those working with children, and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The course can be taken as a stand-alone course but equally offers many students a way in to other Tavistock MA courses and training provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Course Lead will lead the existing course team, ensuring that it is adequately resourced, arranging for the provision of teaching and learning across the course modules and addressing student issues and concerns promptly as they arise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role holder will work with the Tavistock D24 Course Lead ensure that assessment processes are conducted in accordance with Tavistock, University of Essex regulation’s, informed by QAA standards. The role holder will ensure that the quality assurance aspects of the course are maintained through; staff training and updates, staff reviews and evaluation’s of course provision, through addressing external examiners and students feedback, an annual quality review and action plan (REP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role holder will be responsible for ensuring the budget for the course is set and met and that liaison with Communications and Marketing ensures ongoing recruitment, seeking new student markets and opportunities. The post holder will also be responsible for thinking about the ongoing development of the course, ensuring it remains relevant and accessible, and will be involved in course development and delivery (i.e.) technology enhanced learning (TEL) and through possible bespoke and regional developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will need to work and liaise closely with the Tavistock Course Lead for D24 in the shared provision of teaching and learning opportunities on this course, the Course Administrator and other members of DET.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are requested to use the section &quot;Supporting Information&quot; on the application form to set out their reasons for applying and their suitability, referring to the person specification, for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date given is a guide. We reserve the right to close the vacancy once we have received sufficient applications, so we advise you to submit your application as early as possible to prevent disappointment. Candidates suitable for shortlisting will be contacted within three weeks. If you have not heard from us within this time then you have not been successful on this occasion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lydia Hartland-Rowe, Portfolio Manager at lhartland-rowe@tavi-port.nhs.uk or call at 07773 204922&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fiona Phelps, Head of Training, Gloucester Counselling Service or call on 01453 766310&lt;/p&gt;
